data.title: North European Oil Royalty Trust (NYSE: NRT) declares $0.31 per unit distribution for Q4 of fiscal 2025, payable on Nov 26 to owners of record on Nov 14.
data.description: In Keene, New Hampshire, on October 31, 2025, the Trustees of the North European Oil Royalty Trust revealed a quarterly distribution of $0.31 per unit for the last quarter of fiscal 2025. This payment is set to be issued on November 26, 2025, to shareholders registered as owners on November 14, 2025. This amount demonstrates an increase from the previous distribution and showcases the Trust's commitment to its investors.

data.title: Co-Diagnostics, Inc. (NASDAQ: CODX) to release Q3 2025 financial results on Thursday. Salt Lake City. Oct. 31, 2025.
data.description: In Salt Lake City on October 31, 2025, Co-Diagnostics, Inc. (NASDAQ: CODX), a company specializing in molecular diagnostics, revealed plans to unveil its financial performance for the third quarter of 2025. The company's patented platform is tailored for creating molecular diagnostic tests. The exact release date for the financial results is yet to be disclosed.

data.title: Applications open on Nov. 1 for 8 scholarships in Canada for female pilots and aircraft engineers.
data.description: Eight scholarships are being offered to young women in Canada who are pursuing careers as commercial pilots or aircraft maintenance engineers. Among these scholarships, four recipients will be selected as CAE Women in Flight ambassadors. Applications for these scholarships are now open starting November 1st. The initiative is based in Montreal and the announcement was made on October 31, 2025.

data.title: Chinese company CATL sets up battery plant in Germany's Arnstadt, supporting China's 15th Five-Year Plan for development.
data.description: On October 31, 2025, reports from China.org.cn highlighted China's 15th Five-Year Plan, focusing on a modernized battery plant established by Chinese company CATL in Arnstadt, a small town in central Germany. The plant is currently operating at full capacity. Arnstadt, previously a significant location for Germany's economic activities, is now hosting this state-of-the-art facility.

data.title: Urban Outfitters introduces new store concept, city-by-city format with brighter design, targeting Gen Z shoppers. #RetailEvolution
data.description: Urban Outfitters has recently introduced a revamped store concept across various cities, combining a contemporary and adaptable design with merchandising strategies tailored to each market. The new format aims to create a more modern and inviting atmosphere for customers. In Philadelphia, the roll-out of this initiative began on October 31, 2025. This initiative is part of Urban Outfitters' efforts to enhance the retail experience and better cater to the preferences of consumers in different locations.

data.title: Save A Lot launches annual Bags for a Brighter Holiday food donation program; customers can purchase $5.49 bags of food until Dec 24.
data.description: Save A Lot, a leading discount grocery chain in the US, has announced the commencement of its annual Bags for a Brighter Holiday food donation program in St. Louis. This initiative, now in its tenth year, aims to aid local communities by providing essential, top-notch food items to charities combating hunger. Customers can contribute by buying pre-packaged food bags priced at $5.49* at Save A Lot stores across the nation until December 24. The program has been a significant success in supporting hometowns and giving back to those in need.

data.title: HGGC invests in UK energy consultant Inspired, acquiring all shares, with over $8 billion in assets.
data.description: HGGC, a middle-market private equity firm based in Palo Alto, California, recently revealed the completion of their acquisition of Inspired plc. The deal was carried out by Intrepid Bidco Limited, a new entity fully owned by funds managed by HGGC and its affiliates. Inspired plc, a company specializing in tech-enabled energy cost management, now belongs entirely to HGGC. With over $8 billion in assets under management, HGGC continues to focus on fostering partnerships and driving value in the market.

data.title: ArborGen introduces new pine seedling rebrand with AG Scoring System for better reforestation choices.
data.description: A new data-based pine seedling rebrand, known as the AG Scoring System, has been introduced by ArborGen in Summerville, South Carolina. This system aims to provide clearer and more confident guidance for reforestation by utilizing data-driven approaches.

data.title: Dow Jones rises on Amazon and Apple earnings, with Nvidia and Palantir rebounding; live coverage.
data.description: Today, the Dow Jones index saw an increase as Amazon and Apple reported strong earnings, causing a surge in their stock prices. This led to a positive trend in the stock market, with the Dow rising. Other companies like Nvidia and Palantir also experienced a rebound in their stock prices. The market was dynamic, with live coverage capturing these movements. This news update highlights the significance of these tech giants in influencing market trends, emphasizing the role of strong corporate performances in driving stock market activities.

The event will feature top motorcycle and bicycle brands, highlighting the newest trends in the industry. Explore cutting-edge products and innovations from global leaders in the field.

data.description: Introducing a New Level of Sandwich Excellence in Westwood Village WESTWOOD, Calif., Oct. 31, 2025 – BREAD HEAD is thrilled to reveal the launch of its third sandwich store on Saturday, November 1, 2025. Situated in the heart of downtown WESTWOOD VILLAGE, near UCLA's main campus, this exciting new location is set to enhance the local dining scene.

data.title: APUS hosting virtual conference on Nov 6-7 with keynotes from FIFA World Cup 2026 Executive and Emmy Award Winner for Esports. Focus on latest trends in Esports, Sports Science, and Sports Management.
data.description: Today, in Charles Town, West Virginia, a prominent event featured notable speakers such as an Executive for the FIFA World Cup 2026, an Emmy Award-winning individual in Esports, an official from NCAA and the Olympic Volleyball committee, and a specialist in health and wellness. The event highlighted the latest advancements and trends in Esports, sports science, and sports management. This gathering provided valuable insights for attendees and showcased cutting-edge developments in these fields.

data.title: Conduent adds Michael J. Fucci to Board of Directors, effective October 27. Fucci, ex-Deloitte US Chair, has 40+ years of experience in leadership.
data.description: Conduent Incorporated, a leading tech-focused business solutions company (Nasdaq: CNDT), has appointed Michael J. Fucci to its Board of Directors, starting October 27. Fucci, with over 40 years of leadership background, previously held the position of Deloitte US Chair from 2015 to 2019. In this capacity, he was responsible for crucial tasks such as setting enterprise strategy and ensuring leadership success.

data.title: US stock futures rose after a decline on Thursday, with Amazon leading gains. Nasdaq Futures surged 1.21%. Amazon reported net sales of $180.2B, up 13% YoY, and projects $206-213B for Q4, driving its stock up 12.21%.
data.description: U.S. stock futures rose following a previous decline, with major benchmark indices showing gains. Amazon.com Inc. (NASDAQ: AMZN) and Apple Inc. (NASDAQ: AAPL) drove the increase after strong quarterly results. Nasdaq Composite index fell over 350 points due to mixed earnings from Meta Platforms Inc. (NASDAQ: META) and Microsoft Corp. (NASDAQ: MSFT). 10-year Treasury bond yielded 4.11% while two-year bond was at 3.61%. CME Group's FedWatch tool showed a 66.8% chance of interest rate cut in December. Futures changes were: Dow Jones 0.11%, S&P 500 0.69%, Nasdaq 100 1.21%, and Russell 2000 -0.03%. SPDR S&P 500 ETF Trust (NYSE: SPY) and Invesco QQQ Trust ETF (NASDAQ: QQQ) tracking S&P 500 and Nasdaq 100 rose in premarket, with SPY at $685.54 (up 0.84%) and QQQ at $634.65 (up 1.37%). Amazon.com surged 12.21% in premarket after third-quarter net sales of $180.2 billion, predicting fourth-quarter sales between $206.0 billion to $213.0 billion. AMZN maintained a strong price trend in short, medium, and long terms.
